                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d9">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">837.00/1508: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Minister in Cuba</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gonzales</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-02-12T13:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 12, 1919, 1 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Department’s January 24, 1 p.m. and your January 25, 2 p.m.</p>
                <p>You are instructed to keep before President Menocal the substance of Department’s
                    telegram January 24, 1 p.m. and constantly to call to the attention of the Cuban
                    Government the promises made in regard to electoral reforms contained in the
                    note from the Minister of Foreign Affairs to your Legation of January 20,
                        1919.<note n="5" xml:id="d9fn5">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_3">p. 3</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
